# ErlBASIC credentials file
# This is an EXAMPLE file. It needs to be named
#        .credentials
# for the system to recognize it. Do not check in the actual .credentials file
#
# Format: [Project,Programmer] PASSWORD[, Display Name[, other fields...]]
#
# Lines beginning with '#' or '%' are comments.  Blank lines are ignored.
# Passwords are case-insensitive (uppercased before hashing, RSTS/E convention).
# Characters outside the ASR-33 character set (codes 0x20-0x5F after uppercasing)
# are accepted but may cause compatibility issues with teletype clients.
#
# If this file is MISSING the server will print an error and exit.
# If this file is EMPTY (or contains only comments/blank lines) the default
# SYSTEM password is used for the two built-in accounts below.

[0,1] SYSTEM, System Account
[1,1] SYSTEM, System Manager
